A tragic plane crash in Indonesia's West Sulawesi province claimed the lives of at least 90 people, including three Americans from one family.
The Adam Air Boeing 737-400 disappeared from radar screens, prompting criticism of slow search and rescue efforts.
The wreckage was found in a mountainous region near Polewali, with only 12 survivors reported.
The incident, attributed to bad weather and low altitude flying, marks one of Indonesia's worst air disasters.
International condolences poured in as authorities worked to recover the victims, including military personnel, from the crash site.
